Adhesive.name: Adhesive
Adhesive.help-text: List of characters who can generate an adhesive resin or glue or by other means force objects to adhere to one another.

Advanced Longevity.name: Advanced Longevity
Advanced Longevity.help-text: Includes characters who are not true immortals, but do in fact have unnaturally long lifespans.

Aerokinesis.name: Aerokinesis
Aerokinesis.help-text: List of characters with aerokinesis, the ability to manipulate air and gases.

Animal Form.name: Animal Form
Animal Form.help-text: Characters possessing animal-like characteristics or animal forms.

Armor Users.name: Armor Users
Armor Users.help-text: Characters, teams, or organizations who have utilized technological or magical armor.

Art-Based Powers.name: Art-Based Powers
Art-Based Powers.help-text: Powers that could be used only through some form of art like writing, painting, singing, etc.

Astral Projection.name: Astral Projection
Astral Projection.help-text: Characters who can astral project, leaving their bodies behind while their minds and/or spirits leave and go to the Astral Plane.

Astral Trapping.name: Astral Trapping
Astral Trapping.help-text: also called Astral Anchoring or (more colloquially) Intangible Doom is the psychic ability to trap subjects in an astral-projective state.

Atmokinesis.name: Atmokinesis
Atmokinesis.help-text: the ability to manipulate and exert influence with all the natural forces responsible for weather.

Biological Manipulation.name: Biological Manipulation
Biological Manipulation.help-text: Character with the ability to manipulate the biological processes or formation of themselves or others.

Blood-Based Powers.name: Blood-Based Powers
Blood-Based Powers.help-text: Characters or items, whose powers depends on blood or works when coming into contact with blood (their own or someone else's).

Botanopathy.name: Botanopathy
Botanopathy.help-text: Characters able to communicate with plant life, possibly stimulating rapid growth or directing motion.

Bulletproof.name: Bulletproof
Bulletproof.help-text: Characters whose skin is at least tough enough to repel bullets or is able to repel bullets through some means.

Camouflage.name: Camouflage
Camouflage.help-text: List of characters able to hide their presence from people or machines who would otherwise see them.

Captain Universe.name: Captain Universe
Captain Universe.help-text: List of individuals who have been bonded with Captain Universe's Uni-Power.

Chi Manipulation.name: Chi Manipulation
Chi Manipulation.help-text: Characters whose powers originate from the ability to manipulate the body's bio-electric energy known as  Chi/Qi.

Claws.name: Claws
Claws.help-text: Characters who have claws (or talons) extending from their hands or feet.

Collaboration.name: Collaboration
Collaboration.help-text: Characters, whose powers works or amplified in contact with other persons, usually siblings.

Concussive Blasts.name: Concussive Blasts
Concussive Blasts.help-text: List of characters who can produce Concussive Blasts

Cosmic Awareness.name: Cosmic Awareness
Cosmic Awareness.help-text: List of characters who possess some level of Cosmic Awareness.

Darkforce.name: Darkforce
Darkforce.help-text: This is a list of characters who got their powers from Darkforce.

Death Touch.name: Death Touch
Death Touch.help-text: List of characters who can cause near-instantaneous death by simply touching another person.

Density Manipulation.name: Density Manipulation
Density Manipulation.help-text: List of characters who can alter the density of objects, themselves or other people.

Disintegration.name: Disintegration
Disintegration.help-text: List of characters who can cause matter to crumble and break apart, through touch or at a distance, without causing it to explode.

Disruption.name: Disruption
Disruption.help-text: known as Interference (or Disorientation when used on living subjects), is the ability to project a psychic aura (or an EMP) from one's body that disrupts electrical/electromagnetic fields.

Dream-Based Powers.name: Dream-Based Powers
Dream-Based Powers.help-text: Characters, who can manipulate dreams/nightmares, or whose powers depends on dreams/nightmares (their own or someone else's).

Duplication.name: Duplication
Duplication.help-text: List of characters who possess the ability to create duplicates of themselves.

Ebony Blade User.name: Ebony Blade User
Ebony Blade User.help-text: List of characters who have made use of the Ebony Blade.

Elementals.name: Elementals
Elementals.help-text: Any individual who possesses the ability to manipulate one to many of the forces of nature.

Empaths.name: Empaths
Empaths.help-text: List of characters who can read or project emotions of varying degrees of complexity.

Energy Absorption.name: Energy Absorption
Energy Absorption.help-text: Characters with the ability to physically absorb one or more types of energy, be it kinetic, psionic, electromagnetic, thermal, magical, as well as "life energy".

Energy Form.name: Energy Form
Energy Form.help-text: Characters who are, or have the ability to transform into, beings of pure energy.

Energy Manipulation.name: Energy Manipulation
Energy Manipulation.help-text: List of characters who can direct, control, absorb and release one or more forms of energy.

Energy Senses.name: Energy Senses
Energy Senses.help-text: Characters who can sense energy in such a way as to replicate other senses, or who can perceive energy itself, whether it be electromagnetic (magnetic, infrared), psionic, or magical.

Fear-Based Powers.name: Fear-Based Powers
Fear-Based Powers.help-text: Characters who can manipulate, induce, or feed upon fear, or whose powers depend on fear.

Flaming Body.name: Flaming Body
Flaming Body.help-text: Characters who can engulf their bodies on fire, or turn it into a flaming substance like plasma or magma.

Flat Body.name: Flat Body
Flat Body.help-text: Characters whose bodies are or can turn flat like a piece of paper.

Flight.name: Flight
Flight.help-text: List of Characters who can fly though various means, whether with wings, through a mutation, with telekinesis or other psionic power, or technological enhancements.

Force Field.name: Force Field
Force Field.help-text: List of characters who possess the ability to generate a protective force field around themselves or others.

Gaseous Form.name: Gaseous Form
Gaseous Form.help-text: List of characters whose bodies exist or can convert into a gaseous state.

Gel Manifestation.name: Gel Manifestation
Gel Manifestation.help-text: List of characters who secrete, generate, or are made up of a gelatinous material.

Geo-Thermokinesis.name: Geo-Thermokinesis
Geo-Thermokinesis.help-text: the ability to create and/or manipulate magma and/or lava.

Geokinesis.name: Geokinesis
Geokinesis.help-text: the ability to manipulate the land or ground.

Gestalt Characters.name: Gestalt Characters
Gestalt Characters.help-text: Two or more characters (bodies, minds, energies, etc.

Goo Body.name: Goo Body
Goo Body.help-text: Characters whose bodies essentially exist as goopy blobs of semi-liquid or easily mutable material.

Healers.name: Healers
Healers.help-text: This category is in the process of renaming/moving to Category:Healing.

Houngans and Voodoo Priests.name: Houngans and Voodoo Priests

Hydrokinesis.name: Hydrokinesis
Hydrokinesis.help-text: This category is in the process of splitting into Category:Water Generation and Category:Water Manipulation.

Hypercognitive.name: Hypercognitive
Hypercognitive.help-text: Characters whose brains can instinctively or with little effort perform certain complex operations beyond the capability of a normal human mind.

Hypnosis.name: Hypnosis
Hypnosis.help-text: Characters who can control the actions of others through the art of Hypnosis.

Immortals.name: Immortals
Immortals.help-text: This category is in the process of renaming/moving to Category:Immortality.

Imperceptibility.name: Imperceptibility
Imperceptibility.help-text: Characters that are incapable of being perceived or remembered by virtually all individuals.

Infinity Formula.name: Infinity Formula
Infinity Formula.help-text: This is a list of characters who got their powers from the Infinity Formula.

Inodorosity.name: Inodorosity
Inodorosity.help-text: Characters who have the ability to suppress their scent and/or didn't possesses any discernible scent.

Intangibility.name: Intangibility
Intangibility.help-text: also known sometimes as "Phasing",[1] who cannot be touched by solid matter, can walk through walls.

Interdimensional Travelers.name: Interdimensional Travelers
Interdimensional Travelers.help-text: Characters that can travel or have traveled between different realities.

Intuitives.name: Intuitives
Intuitives.help-text: List of characters who have an intuitive or subconscious genius for a complex field of study, excelling in its application without conscious thought.

Invisibility.name: Invisibility
Invisibility.help-text: Characters who have the ability to render themselves invisible to various means of detection.

Leaping.name: Leaping
Leaping.help-text: List of characters with the ability to leap (but not fly) to a superhuman degree, both in height and distance.

Lightforce.name: Lightforce
Lightforce.help-text: This is a list of characters who got their powers from Lightforce.

Liquid Form.name: Liquid Form
Liquid Form.help-text: Characters who bodies can exist in a liquid or semi-liquid state.

Magic Immunity.name: Magic Immunity
Magic Immunity.help-text: Characters who are resistant or immune to magical attacks or spells.

Magicians.name: Magicians
Magicians.help-text: Characters who, by inherent ability and/or training are practitioners of magic.

Matter Absorption.name: Matter Absorption
Matter Absorption.help-text: Characters able to absorb organic and/or inorganic material.

Matter Manipulation.name: Matter Manipulation
Matter Manipulation.help-text: List of characters sometimes known as makers[1] capable of consciously manipulating inorganic, and sometimes organic, matter at the molecular, sub-molecular, atomic, or sub-atomic scale

Medium Awareness.name: Medium Awareness
Medium Awareness.help-text: Characters who have at some point displayed knowledge they exist within any fictional medium.

Mind Control.name: Mind Control
Mind Control.help-text: The ability to control a person's mind or alter their thoughts.

Mutant Intelligence.name: Mutant Intelligence
Mutant Intelligence.help-text: List of mutant characters whose X-Gene has increased their intelligence giving them skills and increased mental aptitude.

Necromancy.name: Necromancy
Necromancy.help-text: List of characters who are Necromancers; they communicate with, manipulate, or reanimate the dead.

Neuralkinesis.name: Neuralkinesis
Neuralkinesis.help-text: Characters who possesses the ability to transfer their neural energy to others to stimulate the brain's motor functions to make them become more intelligent and intuitive, or to slow down the person's cognitive abilities making them less smart and more dependent, and also switch their consciousness to other living bodies or machines.

Night Vision.name: Night Vision
Night Vision.help-text: List of characters who can see in the dark.

Object-Based Powers.name: Object-Based Powers
Object-Based Powers.help-text: Characters who receive their powers from a single object, such as a mystical amulet or the continual use of super drugs.

Old Power.name: Old Power
Old Power.help-text: which allows them to willfully channel an energy force native to the planet Sakaar itself for the purpose of increasing some of their natural attributes to superhuman levels, and also gives wielders very tectonic like abiltes.

Omnilingual.name: Omnilingual
Omnilingual.help-text: List of characters who are Omnilingual; meaning they can understand and translate any language, spoken or written, regardless of origin.

Optic Blasts.name: Optic Blasts
Optic Blasts.help-text: Characters who release various forms of energy from their eyes, known as Optic Blasts[1] or Eyes Beams[2]

Organic Webbing.name: Organic Webbing
Organic Webbing.help-text: Characters who have the ability to organically produce silk webbing from glands inside their hands.

Osteokinesis.name: Osteokinesis
Osteokinesis.help-text: the ability to manipulate the bones in their own bodies.

Pain Suppression.name: Pain Suppression
Pain Suppression.help-text: Characters who can suppress temporarily or permanently, or lack, more or less of their ability to feel pain

Paralysis.name: Paralysis
Paralysis.help-text: Characters who can cause paralysis in others.

Pheromones.name: Pheromones
Pheromones.help-text: Characters who can influence or control the minds of others through the use of pheromones.

Phoenix Force.name: Phoenix Force
